TY  - JOUR
AU  - Yan, Xuemin (Sterling)
AU  - Zhang, Zhe
T1  - Institutional Investors and Equity Returns: Are Short-term Institutions Better Informed?
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/revfin/hhl046
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
SP  - 893
EP  - 924
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We show that the positive relation between institutional ownership and future stock returns documented in Gompers and Metrick (2001) is driven by short-term institutions. Furthermore, short-term institutions' trading forecasts future stock returns. This predictability does not reverse in the long run and is stronger for small and growth stocks. Short-term institutions' trading is also positively related to future earnings surprises. By contrast, long-term institutions' trading does not forecast future returns, nor is it related to future earnings news. Our results are consistent with the view that short-term institutions are better informed and they trade actively to exploit their informational advantage.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/revfin/hhl046
ER  - 



